<div class="cs-content">
  <div class="cs-content__inner">
    <h1>Prospective Postgraduate Students</h1>
  </div>
  <div class="cs-content__inner">

    {# ── WELCOME ── #}
    <section class="cs-pg-intro">
      <div class="cs-pg-intro__text">
        <h2 class="cs-section-label">Your Research Journey Starts Here</h2>
        <p>
          The Department of Computer Science welcomes applications from talented and motivated students
          interested in advancing their knowledge and research skills through postgraduate studies.
          We offer Honours, Master's, and Doctoral (PhD) programmes — each designed to develop
          your expertise and prepare you for leadership in academia or industry.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    {# ── PROGRAMMES AVAILABLE ── #}
    <section class="cs-pg-avail">
      <h2 class="cs-section-label cs-section-label--center">Available Programmes</h2>
      <div class="cs-pg-avail__grid">
        <a href="/postgraduate/honours" class="cs-pg-avail-card">
          <span class="cs-pg-avail-card__type">BSc Hons</span>
          <span class="cs-pg-avail-card__name">Honours</span>
          <span class="cs-pg-avail-card__detail">6 modules + project · 1 year</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/postgraduate/masters" class="cs-pg-avail-card">
          <span class="cs-pg-avail-card__type">MSc</span>
          <span class="cs-pg-avail-card__name">Master's</span>
          <span class="cs-pg-avail-card__detail">Research thesis · 2–3 years</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/postgraduate/phd" class="cs-pg-avail-card">
          <span class="cs-pg-avail-card__type">PhD</span>
          <span class="cs-pg-avail-card__name">Doctoral</span>
          <span class="cs-pg-avail-card__detail">Original research · 3–4 years</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    {# ── ENTRY REQUIREMENTS ── #}
    <section class="cs-pg-admission">
      <h2 class="cs-section-label cs-section-label--center">Entry Requirements</h2>
      <div class="cs-pg-req-grid">
        <div class="cs-pg-req-card">
          <div class="cs-pg-req-card__icon">
            <svg width="28" height="28" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><path d="M22 10v6M2 10l10-5 10 5-10 5z"/><path d="M6 12v5c3 3 9 3 12 0v-5"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="cs-pg-req-card__title">Relevant Degree</h3>
          <p>BSc for Honours, Honours/4-year BSc for MSc, MSc for PhD — in Computer Science or a related field.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="cs-pg-req-card">
          <div class="cs-pg-req-card__icon">
            <svg width="28" height="28" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><path d="M22 12h-4l-3 9L9 3l-3 9H2"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="cs-pg-req-card__title">Academic Excellence</h3>
          <p>Minimum GPA requirements: Honours 60%, Master's 65%, PhD 70%. Strong research potential is valued.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="cs-pg-req-card">
          <div class="cs-pg-req-card__icon">
            <svg width="28" height="28" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><path d="M14 2H6a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v16a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h12a2 2 0 0 0 2-2V8z"/><polyline points="14 2 14 8 20 8"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="cs-pg-req-card__title">Research Alignment</h3>
          <p>Your research interests should align with our departmental strengths and active faculty projects.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="cs-pg-req-card">
          <div class="cs-pg-req-card__icon">
            <svg width="28" height="28" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><path d="M21 15a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H7l-4 4V5a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h14a2 2 0 0 1 2 2z"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="cs-pg-req-card__title">English Proficiency</h3>
          <p>TOEFL/IELTS required for international applicants. All instruction is in English.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    {# ── APPLICATION PROCESS ── #}
    <section class="cs-pg-apply">
      <h2 class="cs-section-label cs-section-label--center">How to Apply</h2>
      <div class="cs-pg-steps">
        <div class="cs-pg-step">
          <span class="cs-pg-step__number">1</span>
          <div class="cs-pg-step__content">
            <h3>Identify Your Research Area</h3>
            <p>Review our <a href="/research">research page</a> and identify faculty members working in your area of interest.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="cs-pg-step">
          <span class="cs-pg-step__number">2</span>
          <div class="cs-pg-step__content">
            <h3>Contact a Potential Supervisor</h3>
            <p>Reach out to faculty members to discuss potential supervision. This strengthens your application significantly.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="cs-pg-step">
          <span class="cs-pg-step__number">3</span>
          <div class="cs-pg-step__content">
            <h3>Submit Your Application</h3>
            <p>Apply through the <a href="https://www.sun.ac.za" target="_blank">university portal</a> with transcripts, CV, statement of research interests, references, and language test scores (if applicable).</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="cs-pg-step">
          <span class="cs-pg-step__number">4</span>
          <div class="cs-pg-step__content">
            <h3>Interview &amp; Admission</h3>
            <p>An interview with potential supervisors is typically conducted. Successful applicants receive a formal offer.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    {# ── DEADLINES ── #}
    <section class="cs-pg-deadlines">
      <h2 class="cs-section-label cs-section-label--center">Application Deadlines</h2>
      <div class="cs-pg-deadlines__grid">
        <div class="cs-pg-deadline-card">
          <span class="cs-pg-deadline-card__period">First Semester</span>
          <span class="cs-pg-deadline-card__date">End of October</span>
          <p>Applications for the following year's first semester intake.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="cs-pg-deadline-card">
          <span class="cs-pg-deadline-card__period">Second Semester</span>
          <span class="cs-pg-deadline-card__date">End of May</span>
          <p>Applications for mid-year intake. Subject to space availability.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="cs-pg-deadline-card">
          <span class="cs-pg-deadline-card__period">Late Applications</span>
          <span class="cs-pg-deadline-card__date">Case by Case</span>
          <p>Late applications may be considered subject to space and supervisor availability.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    {# ── FUNDING ── #}
    <section class="cs-pg-funding">
      <h2 class="cs-section-label cs-section-label--center">Funding Opportunities</h2>
      <div class="cs-pg-funding__grid">
        <div class="cs-pg-funding-item">
          <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"/></svg>
          <h3>Bursaries &amp; Scholarships</h3>
          <p>Merit-based financial support through university and external scholarship programmes.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="cs-pg-funding-item">
          <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><rect x="2" y="3" width="20" height="14" rx="2"/><path d="M8 21h8M12 17v4"/></svg>
          <h3>Teaching Assistantships</h3>
          <p>Earn income by assisting with undergraduate teaching and lab supervision.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="cs-pg-funding-item">
          <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><line x1="2" y1="12" x2="22" y2="12"/><path d="M12 2a15.3 15.3 0 0 1 4 10 15.3 15.3 0 0 1-4 10 15.3 15.3 0 0 1-4-10 15.3 15.3 0 0 1 4-10z"/></svg>
          <h3>Exchange &amp; Mobility Grants</h3>
          <p>International exchange opportunities and mobility grants for research visits abroad.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="cs-pg-funding-item">
          <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><path d="M16 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-4-4H5a4 4 0 0 0-4 4v2"/><circle cx="8.5" cy="7" r="4"/><path d="M20 8v6M23 11h-6"/></svg>
          <h3>Industry-Sponsored Research</h3>
          <p>Funded research projects in partnership with technology companies and organisations.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    {# ── FAQ ── #}
    <section class="cs-pg-faq">
      <h2 class="cs-section-label cs-section-label--center">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div class="cs-pg-faq__list">
        <div class="cs-pg-faq-item">
          <h3 class="cs-pg-faq-item__question">What if my GPA is below the minimum?</h3>
          <p>Strong research potential, relevant work experience, or publications can sometimes compensate. Contact the department to discuss your case.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="cs-pg-faq-item">
          <h3 class="cs-pg-faq-item__question">Do I need a supervisor before applying?</h3>
          <p>We strongly encourage contacting faculty in your area of interest before applying. This ensures a good match and strengthens your application.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="cs-pg-faq-item">
          <h3 class="cs-pg-faq-item__question">Can I study part-time?</h3>
          <p>Yes, most programmes offer part-time options. Honours: up to 2 years, Master's: up to 5 years. Contact the graduate office for details.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="cs-pg-faq-item">
          <h3 class="cs-pg-faq-item__question">What support services are available?</h3>
          <p>Graduate students have access to office space, computing facilities, library resources, graduate seminars, research funding, conference support, and career mentoring.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    {# ── CONTACT ── #}
    <section class="cs-pg-contact">
      <h2 class="cs-section-label cs-section-label--center">Get in Touch</h2>
      <div class="cs-pg-contact__grid">
